      • getAllowRecursiveRoot

        public boolean getAllowRecursiveRoot()
        Flag to know if the root object/hub should allow for recursive duing the find. Default is determined by the following. Default is false, unless hub is the root and it has a masterObject.

      • onFound

        protected void onFound(T obj)
        Add the found object to the list that is returned by find. This can be overwritten to get all of the objects as they are found.
        See Also:
        to be able to have the find stop searching.

      • onDataNotFound

        Called during a find when data was not found. Use stop() to have the find aborted.
